data.text: You can also use more slender and most slender .

data.enText: thin in an attractive or elegant way
a glass with a slender stem
small in amount or size and hardly enough

data.chText: 以微弱优势 / 多数获胜
data.enText: to win by a slender margin/majority
people of slender means (= with little money)

data.chText: 澳大利亚队在上半场终时以1:0的微弱优势领先。
data.enText: Australia held a slender 1–0 lead at half-time.

ex.enText: He was lean, tall and muscular.
He has a lean handsome face.

synonyms.bx: 尤指男人或动物瘦而健壮的。

ex.enText: All girls want to be slender.

ex.chText: 桦树有光滑的树皮和细长的树枝。
ex.enText: The birch has smooth bark and slender branches.

synonyms.bx: 多指女性身材修长苗条、体态优美的；形容物体时表示细或窄的。

ex.chText: 她纤弱的身躯因阵阵咳嗽而颤抖。
ex.enText: Her slight frame was shaken by bouts of coughing.
She is trying to get slim.
She goes for tall slim men.

synonyms.bx: 指人身材修长的，常用于减肥者；也可形容书、钱包等薄的。

ex.chText: 就他的年龄而言，这男孩算是瘦的。
ex.enText: The boy was thin for his age.
She is thin in the face.
She was wearing a thin gold chain.

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，指人或身体部位瘦削的，也可形容物体细或薄的。

tr: being of delicate or slender build
example: she was slender as a willow shoot is slender"- Frank Norri
a slim girl with straight blonde hair
watched her slight figure cross the street

tr: having little width in proportion to the length or height

example: a thin line across the page

value.def: A slender person is attractively thin and graceful.

example.ex: She was slender, with delicate wrists and ankles.
example.tran: 她身量苗条，手腕和脚踝曲线玲珑。

example.ex: ...a tall, slender figure in a straw hat...
example.tran: 头顶草帽、高挑苗条的人影

example.ex: He gazed at her slender neck.
example.tran: 他凝视着她优美的颈部。

value.def: You can use slender to describe a situation which exists but only to a very small degree.

example.ex: The United States held a slender lead...
He has won a vote of confidence but only by a slender majority.
example.tran: 他以微弱多数赢得了信任票。

value.tran: 微弱的;薄弱的;不足的;不充分的
